This paper deals with social choice theory, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The paper presents an algorithm for checking the level-1 consensus property, which involves analyzing preference profiles, and proposes a weaker property called Flexible Consensus. This involves analyzing and manipulating data, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses theoretical probabilities and convergence, which are related to probability theory and statistics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with stability implications of social choice, which is a topic in social informatics (cs.SI).
